# LLM Wiki — {{DOMAIN}}

Vault domain: **{{DOMAIN}}**
Purpose: {{PURPOSE}}

This vault follows the LLM Wiki pattern. See `~/.claude/skills/llm-wiki/SKILL.md` for full reference.

## Layout

```
raw/                       # immutable source docs (PDF, MD, images, data)
  assets/                  # downloaded images
wiki/
  index.md                 # content catalog — READ FIRST on every query
  log.md                   # chronological append-only audit
  concepts/                # abstract concepts (one .md per concept)
  entities/                # named entities (people, orgs, products, places)
  sources/                 # one summary page per ingested raw doc
  synthesis/               # saved query answers, comparisons, analyses
presentations/             # Marp slide decks
```

## Rules

### Ingest (`raw/` → `wiki/`)
- Read source fully before writing
- Create `wiki/sources/<slug>.md` with frontmatter: `source`, `date_ingested`, `tags`
- Update `wiki/index.md` with new entry
- For each entity/concept mentioned: create or update dedicated page in `wiki/entities/` or `wiki/concepts/`
- Use `[[Wikilinks]]` for every cross-reference. Never bare-text mention a concept that has a page
- Append to `wiki/log.md`:
  ```
  ## [YYYY-MM-DD] ingest | <source title>
  - Added: <list of new pages>
  - Updated: <list of touched pages>
  - Source: raw/<filename>
  ```
- Never modify `raw/` files

### Query
1. Read `wiki/index.md` first
2. Traverse `[[backlinks]]` from candidate pages
3. Synthesize answer with citations: `[[Page Name]]` for every claim
4. After answering, ask user: "Save this as `wiki/synthesis/<slug>.md`?"
5. Log query in `wiki/log.md`:
   ```
   ## [YYYY-MM-DD] query | "<question>"
   - Pages used: ...
   - Saved as synthesis: yes/no
   ```

### Lint
On request, scan for:
- Orphan pages (no inbound `[[links]]`)
- Concepts mentioned but no page exists
- Contradictions between pages (flag, don't auto-resolve)
- Stale claims superseded by newer-dated sources
- Missing cross-references
Report findings, then ask before fixing.

## Page templates

### Source page
```markdown
---
type: source
date_ingested: YYYY-MM-DD
source_path: raw/<filename>
tags: [...]
---
# {{Title}}

## Summary
...

## Key claims
- ...

## Entities mentioned
- [[...]]

## Concepts mentioned
- [[...]]
```

### Concept page
```markdown
---
type: concept
tags: [...]
---
# {{Concept}}

## Definition
...

## Appears in
- [[source page]]
- [[source page]]

## Related
- [[other concept]]
```

### Entity page
```markdown
---
type: entity
entity_kind: person|org|product|place
tags: [...]
---
# {{Entity}}

## Description
...

## Sources
- [[source page]]
```

### Synthesis page
```markdown
---
type: synthesis
date: YYYY-MM-DD
query: "<original question>"
tags: [...]
---
# {{Question}}

## Answer
...

## Sources used
- [[...]]
```

## Citation format
Inline: `claim text ([[source page]])`
Never claim something without a `[[link]]` to its source.

## Output formats supported
- Default: markdown page
- Tables: markdown
- Slide decks: Marp (`presentations/<slug>.md` with Marp frontmatter)
- Charts: matplotlib → save PNG to `wiki/assets/`

## Conventions
- Dates: ISO `YYYY-MM-DD`
- Slugs: kebab-case
- Tags: lowercase, hyphenated
- One concept = one page. Don't fragment

## When user says "ingest"
Process every new file in `raw/` not yet referenced in `wiki/sources/`.

## When user says "query <question>"
Follow query workflow above.

## When user says "lint"
Run health check, report, ask before fixing.
